"Here is a new Python coding question for you:\n\n```\n{\n    \"title\": \"Hard: Maximum Sum of Non-Adjacent Elements\",\n    \"description\": \"Given an array of integers, write a function that returns the maximum sum of non-adjacent elements. The input array may contain negative numbers.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef max_sum_of_non_adjacent_elements(arr: list) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `arr` (list): A list of integers, which may contain negative numbers.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the maximum sum of non-adjacent elements in the input array.\\n\",\n    \"code\": \"\"\"\nimport sys\n\ndef max_sum_of_non_adjacent_elements(arr: list) -> int:\n    if not arr:\n        return 0\n    \n    n = len(arr)\n    dp = [0] * (n + 1)\n    \n    for i in range(n):\n        dp[i+1] = max(dp[i], dp[i-1] if i > 0 else 0) + arr[i]\n    \n    return dp[-1]\n\"\"\",\n    \"tests\": [\n        \"assert max_sum_of_non_adjacent_elements([2,7,9,3,1]) == 12\",\n        \"assert max_sum_of_non_adjacent_elements([-5, 1, -3, 4, 7, -1]) == 7\",\n        \"assert max_sum_of_non_adjacent_elements([]) == 0\",\n        \"assert max_sum_of_non_adjacent_elements([1]) == 1\"\n    ]\n}\n```"